partment of Physical Education and Sports plays a vital role in the overall development of students by promoting physical fitness, mental well-being, and sportsmanship. The department is committed to creating a healthy and active environment where students are encouraged to participate in various indoor and outdoor sports activities. Under the guidance of the Director of Physical Education and Sports, the department organizes regular training sessions, inter-class and inter-collegiate competitions, and annual sports events. It also identifies and nurtures talented athletes, providing them with opportunities to compete at district, state, and national levels. Vision & Mission Vision To create a dynamic and inclusive sports environment that promotes physical fitness, mental well-being, and excellence in sports, empowering students to achieve their full potential and lead healthy, active lives. Mission To encourage active participation in sports and physical activities among all students. To identify and nurture talented athletes for higher-level competitions. To organize sports events, tournaments, and wellness programs regularly. To develop physical fitness, discipline, teamwork, and leadership qualities. Program outcomes: Students graduating from the Department of physical Education and sports are expected to: Develop and maintain a high level of physical fitness, endurance, strength, and overall health. Understand the rules, techniques, and strategies of various indoor and outdoor games and sports. Demonstrate proficiency in selected sports and physical activities with proper techniques. Exhibit leadership qualities, teamwork, cooperation, and sportsmanship in all activities. Sports Facilities: • Sports Facilities Documents NSS Activities: • NSS Manual Documents • Life skills Documents 2023-24 • NSS Blood Donation 2023-24 • NSS Health check up 2023-24 • Campainon On Eye Cheek Up-2021-2022 Documents NSS Enrolled Students: • NSS Volenteers List 2025-26 --> Activities